awards.description:
Youth Exchange programme involving 28 young people from France, Greece, Italy, Malta, Romania and Turkey;
Aims: focus on the Human Library method, sustain social growth, solidarity and tolerance, concentrate on experiences among cultural diversity, mutual understanding, and inclusion of people with fewer opportunities, interreligious dialogue, anti-discrimination, gender equality and cultural stereotypes.
Main activities: non-formal and informal learning methods, role play, visiting NGOs, the living library experience with the Living Books, teambuilding activities;

